04/11/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government has decided to add 36 more troops to its contingent deployed in Iraq, Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki announced on Friday (November 2nd). 
"We are glad that as a country aspiring to NATO membership, we can show that even as a candidate, we are ready to share the responsibility in solidarity with our NATO partners," he said. 
The 36 additional troops will join the 44 already there, after approval by parliament. 
Macedonia, Albania, and Croatia hope to be invited to join the Alliance at its summit in Bucharest next spring. 
Skopje also has troops in Afghanistan and Bosnia and Herzegovina. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Reuters, B92, Xinhua - 03/11/07; Reuters, Xinhua - 02/11/07)
